## rigour
metric function := let $X$ be a non-empty set, the function $d: X \times X \to \mathbb{R}$ is called metric if: 
    $d(x,y) > 0$ if $x \neq y$ and $d(x,x) = 0$  non-negative
    $d(x,y) = d(y,x)$ symmetric
    $d(x,z) \le d(x,y) + d(x,z)$ Triangle inequality
