(i) greater than or equal to zero; 
(ii) greater than zero if x and y are distinct; 
(iii) the same as the distance between y and x; and 
(iv) no larger than the sum of the distances produced by taking a detour through a point z. 
We formalize these conditions to define a “metric” on a set.
